content: I do not have personal information about users. however, regarding the sharing of personal information with other organizations, the census bureau is required by law to protect the privacy of individuals and households who participate in the census. the information collected is kept confidential and cannot be shared with any other government agency, law enforcement, or private organization. the census bureau is also prohibited by law from using the information for any purpose other than statistical analysis. in addition, census bureau employees are subject to severe penalties, including imprisonment, for any unauthorized disclosure of confidential information.
